import subprocess

TESTS = [
    ("123\n", "77\n"),  # sample 1
    ("250\n", "50\n"),  # sample 2
    ("1\n", "99\n"),
    ("99\n", "1\n"),
    ("100\n", "100\n"),
    ("199\n", "1\n"),
    ("200\n", "100\n"),
    ("299\n", "1\n"),
]

failures = []
for inp, expected in TESTS:
    p = subprocess.Popen(["python3", "solution.py"], stdin=subprocess.PIPE, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE, text=True)
    out, err = p.communicate(inp)
    out = out
    if out != expected:
        failures.append((inp.strip(), out, expected, err))

if failures:
    print(f"{len(failures)} tests failed")
    for f in failures:
        print("Input:", f[0])
        print("Got:", repr(f[1]))
        print("Expected:", repr(f[2]))
        if f[3]:
            print("Stderr:", f[3])
        print()
    exit(1)
else:
    print("All tests passed")
    exit(0)
